Step-by-step: Run in Django shell
1. Open Terminal

Go to your Django project folder (where manage.py is)

Example:

cd ClinicProject
2. Start Django shell
python manage.py shell

You will see something like:

>>>

That means you are inside Python shell

3. Import your User model

Now type:

from accounts.models import User

Press Enter

4. Get your admin user
user = User.objects.get(username="admin")

Press Enter

5. Set new password (IMPORTANT STEP)
user.set_password("adminadminadmin")



6. Save it
user.save()
 7. Exit shell
exit()


